<p>Looking to bake <a href=3D"https://www.theclevercarrot.com/2014/01/sourd=
ough-bread-a-beginners-guide/">sourdough bread?</a> First: you=E2=80=99ll n=
eed a sourdough starter. Without it, your bread won=E2=80=99t rise. It=E2=
=80=99s the absolute heart and soul of sourdough baking. Creating a sourdou=
gh starter from scratch is not hard to do. However, the process is intimida=
ting, especially for beginners. <em>Let=E2=80=99s change that.</em></p><div=
 id=3D"AdThrive_Content_1_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content adt=
hrive-content-1 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>



<p>Adapted from my bestselling book <strong><em><a href=3D"https://www.amaz=
on.com/Artisan-Sourdough-Made-Simple-Handcrafted/dp/1624144292" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">Artisan Sourdough Made Simple</a>,</em></strong> I will demystify and=
 <em>simplify</em> the process with step-by-step recipe instructions. In ap=
proximately 7+ days (yes, it takes that long- there are no shortcuts) you=
=E2=80=99ll get approximately 1 cup of bubbly, active sourdough starter whi=
ch is more than enough to make bread, including my best <a href=3D"https://=
www.theclevercarrot.com/2014/01/sourdough-bread-a-beginners-guide">sourdoug=
h bread recipe</a> with olive oil (most popular recipe on my blog!). More <=
a href=3D"https://www.theclevercarrot.com/category/sourdough-recipes/">sour=
dough bread recipes</a> here.</p>



<p>Sourdough is more than just a recipe; it=E2=80=99s an<em>&nbsp;understan=
ding.&nbsp;</em>So before we dive in, let=E2=80=99s define.</p>



