=80=9D</strong> and is an indication that your starter is hungry.&nbsp;It a=
lso has a very <strong>distinct smell,</strong> similar to rubbing alcohol =
or gym socks. <strong>This is normal. Don=E2=80=99t freak out.</strong> Any=
 time you see this liquid, it=E2=80=99s best to pour it off before feeding =
it with fresh flour and water.</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_2_tablet" cla=
